Program: Outlook
Title: How to Embarrass your Dad
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/w3csvr1b
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 27 Nov 2017
Born in a refugee camp in Syria, Ahmad Joudeh grew up with a dream of one day becoming a ballet dancer, but his father had other ideas. In Nigeria Laolu Senbanjo's career had been mapped out by his dad, he became a lawyer, but he really wanted to be an artist. (Photo: Man with his head in his hands. Credit: Stockbyte/Getty Images) Show less